---
import FAQItem from './FAQItem.astro';
---
<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="faq-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">Frequently asked</span>
      <h2>Christ Note FAQ.</h2>
      <p class="faq-lede">Everything you need to know — capture, AI summary, Bible study, and pricing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <FAQItem question="What is Christ Note?">
        An iPhone companion for sermons and Scripture. Capture a homily three ways — record it live, paste a YouTube link, or photograph your notes — and Christ Note delivers an AI summary with scripture references, themes, and quotable lines. The full 66-book Bible is built in, with on-demand study tools (SOAP, passage analysis, chapter headings) and a shared daily devotional.
      </FAQItem>
      <FAQItem question="How does Christ Note protect my privacy?">
        Transcription runs on-device with Whisper — we never receive your raw audio, only the transcript when you ask for a summary. Bible verses are served from a verified text cache so quotes are never hallucinated. Your library syncs to private, encrypted storage tied to your account, and we never sell or share what you record. App install attribution uses <strong>AppsFlyer</strong> with Apple's <strong>SKAdNetwork 4.0</strong> — anonymous, aggregate, no user-level tracking.
      </FAQItem>
      <FAQItem question="Can I use Christ Note offline?">
        Yes for capture and reading. Recording, photo OCR, and the entire 66-book Bible all work without a connection. AI summaries, the daily devotional, and "chat with this sermon" need the internet — they sync the next time you're online.
      </FAQItem>
      <FAQItem question="Is Christ Note free?">
        The free tier lets you try one AI sermon summary, plus a few Bible study tools (SOAP, passage analysis, unlimited chapter headings) — enough to feel how it works. <strong>Christ Note Pro</strong> unlocks unlimited summaries, flashcards, quizzes, sermon chat, and deeper Bible analysis.
      </FAQItem>
      <FAQItem question="Is there an Android app?">
        Not yet. Christ Note is built natively for iPhone (iOS 17+) and uses on-device transcription and Apple Sign-In. Android isn't on the immediate roadmap — join the waitlist and we'll write if that changes.
      </FAQItem>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.faq {
  padding: var(--section-y) 0 0;
}
.faq-head {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: var(--s-12);
}
.faq-head .eyebrow {
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: var(--s-4);
}
.faq-head h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--fs-display-3);
  font-weight: 500;
  margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
}
.faq-lede {
  font-family: "Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif;
  font-style: italic;
  font-size: var(--fs-body-lg);
  color: var(--ink-600);
  max-width: 52ch;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
.faq-list {
  max-width: 760px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
.faq-list :global(.faq-answer strong) {
  color: var(--ink-900);
  font-weight: 600;
}
</style>
